We are in a situation
that is beyond morality. Hm?

497
00:56:14,560 --> 00:56:17,280
Your wife is dead.

498
00:56:17,520 --> 00:56:22,800
How do you know? How can you be definitive
about a construct you do not understand?

499
00:56:23,040 --> 00:56:25,600
She's a copy. A facsimile.

500
00:56:25,840 --> 00:56:29,040
And she's seducing you all over again.

501
00:56:29,280 --> 00:56:32,920
You're sick.

502
00:56:36,160 --> 00:56:40,360
We are not taking her back with us.

503
00:57:50,880 --> 00:57:54,560
Leave the light off.

504
00:58:05,840 --> 00:58:09,520
You think you're dreaming me.

505
00:58:09,760 --> 00:58:11,680
You're not Gibarian.

506
00:58:11,920 --> 00:58:14,480
No?

507
00:58:14,720 --> 00:58:17,760
Who am I, then?

508
00:58:18,000 --> 00:58:20,640
- A puppet.
- And you're not?

509
00:58:20,880 --> 00:58:23,200
Well, maybe you're my puppet.

510
00:58:23,440 --> 00:58:27,040
But like all puppets,
you think you're actually human.

511
00:58:27,280 --> 00:58:31,760
That's the puppet's dream - being human.

512
00:58:36,720 --> 00:58:39,440
Why did you kill yourself?

513
00:58:39,680 --> 00:58:43,360
It seemed like a good idea
at the time. Now I think I made a mistake.

514
00:58:43,600 --> 00:58:47,840
- What about your son?
- That's not my son. My son is on Earth.

515
00:58:48,080 --> 00:58:54,360
And that's not your wife.
They are part of Solaris. Remember that.

516
00:58:57,680 --> 00:59:00,480
What does Solaris want from us?

517
00:59:00,720 --> 00:59:04,000
Why do you think it has to want something?

518
00:59:04,240 --> 00:59:09,840
This is why you have to leave.
If you keep thinking there is a solution...

519
00:59:10,080 --> 00:59:12,400
you'll die here.

520
00:59:12,640 --> 00:59:15,240
I can't leave her.

521
00:59:15,280 --> 00:59:17,840
I'll figure it out.

522
00:59:18,080 --> 00:59:20,880
Do you understand
what I'm trying to tell you?

523
00:59:21,120 --> 00:59:23,440
There are no answers.

524
00:59:23,680 --> 00:59:27,320
Only choices.

525
00:59:45,920 --> 00:59:49,200
Rheya?

526
00:59:54,880 --> 00:59:58,160
Rheya?

527
01:00:08,720 --> 01:00:11,960
Rheya?

528
01:00:29,120 --> 01:00:32,400
Rheya?

529
01:00:38,400 --> 01:00:41,840
Gordon!

530
01:01:20,320 --> 01:01:25,320
- What happened?
- She drank liquid oxygen.

531
01:01:47,840 --> 01:01:51,320
She's dead.

532
01:01:52,000 --> 01:01:54,880
No.

533
01:02:14,960 --> 01:02:21,200
I never get used to them.
These... resurrections.

534
01:03:17,200 --> 01:03:20,640
Oh, no.

535
01:03:21,200 --> 01:03:24,480
No.

536
01:03:29,600 --> 01:03:33,480
Why'd you do that?

537
01:03:34,240 --> 01:03:35,440
Rheya?

538
01:03:35,680 --> 01:03:39,520
Don't call me that.

539
01:03:46,480 --> 01:03:49,040
<i>There are two components.</i>

540
01:03:49,280 --> 01:03:55,120
A high-energy proton accelerator
and a matter phase modulator.

541
01:03:55,360 --> 01:04:01,120
By adjusting the tuning frequency I get an
enhancement of Higgs antibosons at 90GHz

542
01:04:01,360 --> 01:04:05,280
and an almost pure beam at 160GHz.

543
01:04:05,520 --> 01:04:09,360
I used it on mine.

544
01:04:09,600 --> 01:04:11,360
What happens?

545
01:04:11,600 --> 01:04:16,440
They disappear,
back where they came from.

546
01:04:19,520 --> 01:04:23,280
It's what she wants.

547
01:04:23,680 --> 01:04:27,520
I won't let her do it.

548
01:04:27,600 --> 01:04:32,080
She'll come to me when you're asleep.

549
01:04:33,680 --> 01:04:37,640
Then I won't sleep.

550
01:04:39,360 --> 01:04:42,160
<i>Don't you see?
I came from your memory of her.</i>

551
01:04:42,400 --> 01:04:46,400
<i>That's the problem. I'm not a whole person.</i>

552
01:04:46,640 --> 01:04:51,120
In your memory
you get to control everything.

553
01:04:51,200 --> 01:04:55,840
So even if you remember something wrong,
I am predetermined to carry it out.

554
01:04:56,080 --> 01:04:58,400
I'm suicidal because
that's how you remember me.

555
01:04:58,640 --> 01:05:02,960
My voice sounds the way it does
because that's how you remember it.

556
01:05:03,200 --> 01:05:07,360
I don't believe that we're
predetermined to relive our past.

557
01:05:07,600 --> 01:05:11,840
I think that we can choose to do it differently.

558
01:05:12,080 --> 01:05:18,560
The day I left and you said you wouldn't make
it, I didn't hear you because I was angry.

559
01:05:18,800 --> 01:05:22,320
This is my chance to undo that mistake.

560
01:05:22,560 --> 01:05:24,960
And I need you to help me.

561
01:05:25,200 --> 01:05:29,400
But am I really Rheya?

562
01:05:32,640 --> 01:05:35,520
I don't know any more.

563
01:05:35,760 --> 01:05:40,120
All I see is you.

564
01:06:10,320 --> 01:06:14,160
All I see is you.

565
01:06:21,600 --> 01:06:25,240
It created me.

566
01:06:25,680 --> 01:06:29,960
And yet I can't communicate with it.

567
01:06:31,360 --> 01:06:33,920
It must hear me, though.

568
01:06:34,160 --> 01:06:38,440
It must know what's happening to me.

569
01:06:38,640 --> 01:06:42,720
And you and I, we would
have to have some kind of...

570
01:06:42,960 --> 01:06:47,000
an arrangement, some kind of...

571
01:06:50,320 --> 01:06:53,920
unspoken understanding...

572
01:06:54,160 --> 01:06:58,200
that I'm not really a human being.

573
01:07:00,000 --> 01:07:03,480
No, Rheya.

574
01:07:07,360 --> 01:07:09,280
Chris...

575
01:07:09,520 --> 01:07:13,520
Chris, I wish you would just
let them use the device on me.

576
01:07:13,760 --> 01:07:21,120
And then you can go back to Earth
and you can tell everybody all about Solaris.

577
01:07:23,040 --> 01:07:25,040
No.

578
01:07:25,280 --> 01:07:30,160
It's the only solution that makes any sense.

579
01:07:30,480 --> 01:07:34,400
We could never have
a life together on Earth, Chris.

580
01:07:34,640 --> 01:07:38,080
You know that.

581
01:07:38,240 --> 01:07:41,280
It would be impossible.

582
01:07:41,520 --> 01:07:45,680
And this? What kind of life is this?

583
01:07:45,920 --> 01:07:47,680
Trapped here.

584
01:07:47,920 --> 01:07:51,120
It's not a life.

585
01:07:51,360 --> 01:07:53,840
I don't know what to call it.

586
01:07:54,080 --> 01:07:57,360
It's what we have.

587
01:07:57,600 --> 01:07:59,600
It's enough for me.

588
01:07:59,840 --> 01:08:02,400
You need to rest.

589
01:08:02,640 --> 01:08:06,480
You're going to make yourself ill.

590
01:08:06,720 --> 01:08:12,080
- I don't care.
- Just lie down for a moment.

591
01:08:12,320 --> 01:08:14,000
Please, Chris.

592
01:08:14,240 --> 01:08:17,880
You have to rest.

593
01:08:45,520 --> 01:08:49,680
You know I'm not human
so I don't understand what you're afraid of.

594
01:08:49,920 --> 01:08:52,160
Of course you can use the device.

595
01:08:52,400 --> 01:08:55,680
It's not murder. You said that yourself.

596
01:08:55,920 --> 01:08:59,360
You're the one who had
the idea in the first place.

597
01:08:59,600 --> 01:09:03,680
Chris doesn't trust me. He...

598
01:13:44,480 --> 01:13:49,520
<i>Chris, don't blame Gordon.</i>

599
01:13:50,240 --> 01:13:54,680
<i>It's not her fault. I begged her to do it.</i>

600
01:13:55,440 --> 01:13:58,480
<i>It's better this way.</i>

601
01:13:58,720 --> 01:14:01,600
<i>I found the suicide note.</i>

602
01:14:01,840 --> 01:14:04,800
<i>I went through your things.</i>

603
01:14:05,040 --> 01:14:09,120
<i>The page torn from the book of poems.</i>

604
01:14:09,360 --> 01:14:13,160
<i>And I realised...</i>

605
01:14:13,240 --> 01:14:14,960
<i>I'm not her.</i>

606
01:14:15,200 --> 01:14:18,640
<i>I'm not Rheya.</i>

607
01:14:18,760 --> 01:14:21,680
<i>I know you loved me, though.</i>

608
01:14:21,920 --> 01:14:25,120
<i>I know that. I felt that.</i>

609
01:14:25,360 --> 01:14:27,760
<i>And I love you.</i>

610
01:14:28,000 --> 01:14:33,120
<i>I wish we could just
live inside that feeling forever.</i>

611
01:14:33,760 --> 01:14:37,680
<i>Maybe there's a place where we can.</i>

612
01:14:37,920 --> 01:14:40,040
<i>But I know it's not on Earth.</i>

613
01:14:40,280 --> 01:14:44,160
<i>And it's not on this ship.</i>

614
01:14:45,440 --> 01:14:49,360
<i>That's all I can say right now.</i>

615
01:15:10,200 --> 01:15:11,600
- You killed her!
- Not her. It.

616
01:15:11,840 --> 01:15:15,520
- It's murder!
- Kelvin, she begged me. It wasn't painful.

617
01:15:15,760 --> 01:15:17,000
- She'll be back!
- No.

618
01:15:17,240 --> 01:15:19,840
- Why would you let her do it?!
- Kelvin!

619
01:15:20,080 --> 01:15:21,840
It's not human!

620
01:15:22,080 --> 01:15:26,320
Whatever it is, it's not human,
and I'm threatened by that.

621
01:15:26,560 --> 01:15:29,200
And I wanna win. I want humans to win.

622
01:15:29,440 --> 01:15:33,240
Whose side are you on?

623
01:15:33,360 --> 01:15:39,800
- What are you doing?
- Putting the Al back online. I'm going home.

624
01:15:52,880 --> 01:15:56,120
Gordon.

625
01:15:57,360 --> 01:16:00,600
Gordon!

626
01:16:23,040 --> 01:16:26,480
- I knew it.
- How long you think he's been dead?

627
01:16:26,720 --> 01:16:31,160
Hard to say because of the cold.

628
01:16:31,280 --> 01:16:34,960
He attacked me.

629
01:16:36,320 --> 01:16:39,600
There I am. Somehow, there I am.

630
01:16:39,840 --> 01:16:45,360
And I couldn't tell you how I'm there,
or who I am or what's going on.

631
01:16:45,600 --> 01:16:48,960
But before I can get to that,

632
01:16:49,200 --> 01:16:51,360
what's this over here?

633
01:16:51,600 --> 01:16:55,040
Comin' at me. What...
what are you tryin' to do?

634
01:16:55,280 --> 01:16:58,240
Oh, I see. You're tryin' to kill me.

635
01:16:58,480 --> 01:17:02,320
Yeah, confusing. I'll tell you somethin'
confusing. Bingo, there you are,

636
01:17:02,560 --> 01:17:06,040
and my welcoming committee
dropped his knife and it's good night.

637
01:17:06,280 --> 01:17:10,400
And, oh, by the way, after all that I find, uh...

638
01:17:10,640 --> 01:17:15,200
this, uh, whoever this... I get my first
good look at it and it happens to be...

639
01:17:15,440 --> 01:17:18,320
I survive the first 30 seconds of this...

640
01:17:18,560 --> 01:17:22,320
life, whatever you wanna call it...
by killing someone.

641
01:17:22,560 --> 01:17:27,800
And, oh, ah, by killing someone
who happens to be me.

642
01:17:27,840 --> 01:17:32,720
See, most people... I would think most people
in this position would be, like "This... ah."

643
01:17:32,960 --> 01:17:37,480
"I don't know." However, this is at least...
This is an incredible opportunity.

644
01:17:37,720 --> 01:17:41,200
This is... What if this is a gift? I'm a gift.

645
01:17:41,440 --> 01:17:44,920
Hey.

646
01:17:46,960 --> 01:17:51,200
I say we use the Higgs device on him.

647
01:17:54,560 --> 01:17:56,800
Mm. Mm-mm.

648
01:17:57,040 --> 01:18:01,640
I don't think you really have time.

649
01:18:01,920 --> 01:18:05,680
Why would you say that?

650
01:18:05,720 --> 01:18:09,040
Well, you know, ever since
we used the famous Higgs device,

651
01:18:09,280 --> 01:18:14,160
Solaris started taking on mass exponentially.

652
01:18:14,280 --> 01:18:18,400
You might have noticed
how we're a lot closer to it.

653
01:18:18,640 --> 01:18:22,640
That would be because everything
within its gravitational field -

654
01:18:22,880 --> 01:18:26,720
it's pulling it in.

655
01:18:27,240 --> 01:18:29,360
Ah, and, yeah, sorry. By the way,

656
01:18:29,600 --> 01:18:35,680
the Higgs device also
drained the fuel cell reactors.

657
01:18:39,240 --> 01:18:43,000
Uh, if... Can I make a suggestion?

658
01:18:43,240 --> 01:18:48,000
I mean, this is... You can do what you want,
but I would just lock me in here really tight

659
01:18:48,240 --> 01:18:52,320
and take the "Athena" back.

660
01:18:54,640 --> 01:18:58,560
Wear your seat belt.

661
01:19:53,280 --> 01:19:55,680
Switch to internal power.

662
01:19:55,920 --> 01:19:59,200
Start fuel cell operational diagnostic.

663
01:19:59,440 --> 01:20:02,320
Service check on LGA.

664
01:20:02,560 --> 01:20:05,520
Point and calibrate high-beam antenna.

665
01:20:05,760 --> 01:20:09,280
Depressurising. Spin all turbines to standby.

666
01:20:09,520 --> 01:20:12,800
Disengage coupling interlocks
and all docking couplers.

667
01:20:13,040 --> 01:20:17,800
Vent and seal
all main engine propellant lines.

668
01:20:33,520 --> 01:20:36,040
<i>Earth.</i>

669
01:20:36,280 --> 01:20:39,960
<i>Even the word sounded strange to me now.</i>

670
01:20:40,200 --> 01:20:43,680
<i>Unfamiliar.</i>

671
01:20:45,840 --> 01:20:48,880
<i>How long had I been gone?</i>

672
01:20:49,120 --> 01:20:52,160
<i>How long had I been back?</i>

673
01:20:52,400 --> 01:20:56,040
<i>Did it matter?</i>

674
01:20:59,120 --> 01:21:04,400
<i>I tried to find the rhythm
of the world where I used to live.</i>

675
01:21:04,640 --> 01:21:07,480
<i>I followed the current.</i>

676
01:21:07,720 --> 01:21:11,440
<i>I was silent and attentive.</i>

677
01:21:11,680 --> 01:21:15,200
<i>I made a conscious effort to smile...</i>

678
01:21:15,440 --> 01:21:17,360
<i>nod...</i>

679
01:21:17,600 --> 01:21:19,920
<i>stand...</i>

680
01:21:20,160 --> 01:21:26,400
<i>and perform the millions of gestures
that constitute life on Earth.</i>

681
01:21:27,920 --> 01:21:33,600
<i>I studied these gestures
until they became reflexes again.</i>

682
01:21:35,040 --> 01:21:37,680
<i>But I was haunted by the idea</i>

683
01:21:37,920 --> 01:21:41,840
<i>that I remembered her wrong.</i>

684
01:21:44,000 --> 01:21:48,480
<i>That somehow I was wrong about everything.</i>

685
01:22:49,240 --> 01:22:54,000
Depressurising.
Spin all turbines to standby.

686
01:22:54,240 --> 01:22:58,040
Disengage coupling interlocks
and all docking couplers.

687
01:22:58,280 --> 01:23:03,080
Vent and seal
all main engine propellant lines.

688
01:24:03,520 --> 01:24:06,080
Rheya!

689
01:24:13,440 --> 01:24:16,880
Rheya?

690
01:26:24,320 --> 01:26:27,800
Chris?

691
01:26:28,160 --> 01:26:31,400
Chris?

692
01:27:09,360 --> 01:27:13,600
Am I alive... or dead?

693
01:27:15,720 --> 01:27:20,160
We don't have to think like that any more.

694
01:27:22,640 --> 01:27:26,400
We're together now.

695
01:27:27,520 --> 01:27:31,520
Everything we've done is forgiven.

696
01:27:31,760 --> 01:27:35,000
Everything.

